{"cursor":"15493","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"\n\n\n\n'Hospital Emergency Codes' are used in hospitals worldwide to alert staff to\nvarious emergencies. The use of codes is intended to convey essential\ninformation quickly and with minimal misunderstanding to staff, while preventing\nstress and panic among visitors to the hospital. These codes may be posted on\nplacards throughout the hospital, or printed on employee identification badges\nfor ready reference. showing disaster codes.]]\n\nHospital emergency codes may denote different events at different hospitals,\nincluding nearby ones. Because many physicians work at more than one\nfacility, this may lead to confusion in emergencies, so uniform systems have\nbeen proposed.\n","linknr":284,"url":"Code_Blue_(emergency_code)","recorded":1362896638,"links":19,"instances":["missouri"],"pdf":["http://www.saiglobal.com/PDFTemp/Previews/OSH/as/as4000/4000/4083.pdf","http://www-med.stanford.edu/shs/update/archives/DEC2002/codes.pdf","http://www.thedacare.org/ThedaCareWeb/Documents/Upload%5C1f9b6419-e20c-4dfe-82c3-2f6f23b0355c.HospitalEmergencyCodestable040705.pdf","http://www.fernocan.com/cbrn_prgm/cbrn.../3bi-2_Emerg_Codes.pdf"],"categories":["Hospitals|Emergency codes","Medical terminology|Emergency codes","Emergency communication"],"headings":["Color code standardization","Codes by color","Codes by emergency","References","External links"],"image":["//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/f/f4/Ambox_content.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/9/99/Question_book-new.svg/50px-Question_book-new.svg.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/0/03/WBH-Troy_disaster_codes.jpg/220px-WBH-Troy_disaster_codes.jpg","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/images/magnify-clip.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/vector/images/search-ltr.png?303-4","//bits.wikimedia.org/images/wikimedia-button.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/images/poweredby_mediawi